THE South African Broadcasting Corporation (SABC) has announced that it has parted ways with Mpho "Mo G" Madise. In a statement, public broadcaster said the recent development comes after the termination of his contract, due to a material breach of contract." Metro FM business manager Ms Kina Nhlengethwa stated that Metro FM will communicate in due course who will take over the show and big thank you to the team that has held Fort during this period." read the statement. On 05 July Daily Sun published a story under the headline "Metro FM presenter manhandled during a BEAMER fight!" READ: Metro FM presenter manhandled during a BEAMER fight! This is after blogger Jabu Brown accused Mo G of refusing to return the car that he has landed to him to test drive for his show. Jabu claimed he gave Mo G his BMW X3 on Wednesday, 29 June and he was meant to return it on Friday, 1 July but when the day arrived Mo G was nowhere to be found. After following Mo G's gig guide Jabu was able to track him and the car down, but before he could hand over the keys to the car, the two got involved in the brawl, which was caught on camera.  Jabu said the car was specifically for the car feature segment on Mo G's show on Metro FM not for his personal use.